Day 8: useEffect Basics
What is useEffect?

useEffect is a React Hook used to perform side effects.

Examples:

Fetch data from an API
Update document title
Run code when a component loads
Set timers
Syntax
import { useEffect } from "react";

useEffect(() => {
    console.log("Component Loaded");
}, []);
Explanation
useEffect(() => {
    // code
}, []);
First argument → function to execute
Second argument → dependency array
Example 1: Run Once on Component Load

Create UseEffectDemo.jsx

import { useEffect } from "react";

function UseEffectDemo() {

    useEffect(() => {
        console.log("Component Loaded");
    }, []);

    return (
        <div>
            <h2>useEffect Demo</h2>
        </div>
    );
}

export default UseEffectDemo;
